2 To amend and reenact R.S. 40:1615(A)(4) and to enact R.S. 40:1615(A)(5) and (6), relative
3 to fire fighting foam; to provide for Class B fire fighting foam containing fluorinated
4 organic chemicals; to provide for definitions; and to provide for related matters.
5 Be it enacted by the Legislature of Louisiana:
6 Section 1. R.S. 40:1615(A)(4) is hereby amended and reenacted and R.S.
7 40:1615(A)(5) and (6) are hereby enacted to read as follows:
8 §1615. Class B fire fighting foam containing fluorinated organic chemicals;
9 definitions; use restrictions
10 A. As used in this Part, the following terms have the meaning ascribed to
11 them in this Section, unless the context clearly indicates otherwise:
12 * * *
13 (4) "Testing" means calibration testing, conformance testing, or fixed system
14 testing the evaluation of fire fighting equipment, systems, or foam concentrates
15 for operability, performance verification, calibration, conformance to
16 manufacturer specifications, or regulatory compliance including but not limited
17 to discharge testing of fixed fire suppression systems, mobile apparatus testing,
18 proportioning system calibrations, and system acceptance testing. "Testing"
19 does not include emergency fire fighting operations.
20 (5) "Training" means instruction, drills, exercises, demonstrations, or
21 other activities conducted to familiarize personnel with the deployment,
22 handling, storage, mixing, proportioning, or application of fire fighting foam,
23 including live fire exercises and simulated fire response scenarios. "Training"
24 does not include emergency fire fighting operations.
